    <statement>
        <p>
Use technology to complete the following table of values.
<me>f(x)=\frac{ x^{2} + 9 \, x }{ x^{2} + 4 \, x }</me>
            <me>
\begin{array}{c|ccccccc}
x &amp; -0.1&amp; -0.01&amp; -0.001&amp; 0&amp; 0.001&amp; 0.01&amp; 0.1 \\\hline
f(x) &amp; &amp; &amp; &amp; &amp; &amp; &amp;  \\
\end{array}
            </me>
        </p>
        <p>
Then explain how to use it to make an educated guess as to the value of
the limit <me>\lim_{ x\to 0 } \frac{ x^{2} + 9 \, x }{ x^{2} + 4 \, x }</me>
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            <me>
\begin{array}{c|ccccccc}
x &amp; -0.1&amp; -0.01&amp; -0.001&amp; 0&amp; 0.001&amp; 0.01&amp; 0.1 \\\hline
f(x) &amp; 2.28205&amp; 2.25313&amp; 2.25031&amp; DNE&amp; 2.24969&amp; 2.24688&amp; 2.21951 \\
\end{array}
            </me>
        </p>
        <p>
The limit is <m>2.25</m>.
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
